<subSubSection id="84882391A52D6A07B8CDFEF7FD07FEEB" pageId="2" pageNumber="1089" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="CC2D701AA52D6A07B8CDFEF7FD07FEEB" blockId="2.[178,1086,299,379]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1089">
Comment 
<taxonomicName id="0B920B99A52D6A07B921FEF7FDF5FED1" authorityName="BERNHAUER" authorityYear="1922" box="[350,542,299,320]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Echiaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="1089" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unicolor">
<emphasis id="FEE6AC08A52D6A07B921FEF7FDF5FED1" box="[350,542,299,320]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1089">Echiaster unicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is rather common in 
<collectingCountry id="B485308AA52D6A07BB7AFEF7FCBFFED0" box="[773,852,299,321]" name="Taiwan" pageId="2" pageNumber="1089">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
. In 
<collectingCountry id="B485308AA52D6A07BB00FEF7FC55FED0" box="[895,958,299,321]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="1089">China</collectingCountry>
, the species was previously known from 
<collectingRegion id="0E56BEF8A52D6A07B99AFE94FDA9FECF" box="[485,578,328,350]" country="China" name="Zhejiang" pageId="2" pageNumber="1089">Zhejiang</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="0E56BEF8A52D6A07BA2EFE94FD4FFECC" box="[593,676,328,349]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="2" pageNumber="1089">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion id="0E56BEF8A52D6A07BA9EFE94FCCFFECC" box="[737,804,328,349]" country="China" name="Hunan" pageId="2" pageNumber="1089">Hunan</collectingRegion>
provinces (
<bibRefCitation id="A8030DEBA52D6A07BBDCFE94FBD9FECF" author="ASSING V" box="[931,1074,328,350]" journalOrPublisher="Beitrage zur Entomologie, Keltern" pageId="2" pageNumber="1089" pagination="413 - 453" part="61" refId="ref4518" refString="ASSING V. (2011): A revision of Sclerochiton (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Beitrage zur Entomologie, Keltern 61 (2): 413 - 453." title="A revision of Sclerochiton (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae)" type="journal article" year="2011">ASSING 2011</bibRefCitation>
). The currently known distribution is illustrated in 
<figureCitation id="54A96C9FA52D6A07BADAFEBAFD03FEEB" box="[677,744,357,379]" captionStart="Map 1" captionStartId="1.[178,223,1240,1261]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,558,1214]" captionTargetId="figure-142@1.[178,1085,558,1214]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Map 1: Distribution of Echiaster species in Asia. Echiaster discrepans (white circles); E. bivirgatus (white diamonds); E. maior (white triangles); E. paulexcisus (black diamond); E. unicolor (black circles)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5361369" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5361369/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="1089">Map 1</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
